       )

     


  [1]: https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/operator_precedence

Indexes start at 0, So if you want to index the last character of a string you have to index the length of it -1.

For example, let string S = &quot;hello!&quot;
S[0] = &#39;h&#39;
Size of S is 6, but the highest index is `S[size-1]` which is `S[5]` = &#39;!&#39;
To fix your code, you must change dni[dni.size()] to dni[dni-size()-1].

